{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.4",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 4,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 4",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 4 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.4.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:1",
      "text": "Then Eliphaz the Temanite answered,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.4.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:2",
      "text": "“If someone ventures to talk with you, will you be grieved? But who can withhold himself from speaking?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.4.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:3",
      "text": "Behold, you have instructed many, you have strengthened the weak hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.4.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:4",
      "text": "Your words have supported him who was falling, you have made the feeble knees firm.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.4.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:5",
      "text": "But now it has come to you, and you faint. It touches you, and you are troubled.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.4.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:6",
      "text": "Isn’t your piety your confidence? Isn’t the integrity of your ways your hope?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.4.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:7",
      "text": "“ Remember, now, who ever perished, being innocent? Or where were the upright cut off?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.4.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:8",
      "text": "According to what I have seen, those who plow iniquity and sow trouble, reap the same.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.4.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:9",
      "text": "By the breath of God they perish. By the blast of his anger are they consumed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.4.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:10",
      "text": "The roaring of the lion, and the voice of the fierce lion, the teeth of the young lions, are broken.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.4.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:11",
      "text": "The old lion perishes for lack of prey. The cubs of the lioness are scattered abroad.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.4.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:12",
      "text": "“ Now a thing was secretly brought to me. My ear received a whisper of it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.4.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:13",
      "text": "In thoughts from the visions of the night, when deep sleep falls on men,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.4.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:14",
      "text": "fear came on me, and trembling, which made all my bones shake.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.4.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:15",
      "text": "Then a spirit passed before my face. The hair of my flesh stood up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.4.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:16",
      "text": "It stood still, but I couldn’t discern its appearance. A form was before my eyes. Silence, then I heard a voice, saying,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.4.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:17",
      "text": "‘ Shall mortal man be more just than God? Shall a man be more pure than his Maker?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.4.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:18",
      "text": "Behold, he puts no trust in his servants. He charges his angels with error.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.4.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:19",
      "text": "How much more those who dwell in houses of clay, whose foundation is in the dust, who are crushed before the moth!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.4.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:20",
      "text": "Between morning and evening they are destroyed. They perish forever without any regarding it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.4.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:21",
      "text": "Isn’t their tent cord plucked up within them? They die, and that without wisdom.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
